A few weeks ago at my clinic, I tried something different. Instead of putting another post out there and waiting, I sent an email to our existing list. Families we‚Äôd worked with before, parents who had enquired but never started, current clients, waitlist families, and even referrers we hadn‚Äôt spoken to in a while.

It's time for another Diplomate Spotlight! In honor of Black History Month, we are highlighting some of our amazing, brilliant black Diplomates during the month of February. Today, we're featuring Dr. Lisa Bolden, Psy.D. With over 25 years of experience, Dr. Bolden is a licensed clinical psychologist dedicated to providing compassionate, research-backed therapy to individuals, couples, families, and groups. Specializing in Cognitive Behavioral Therapy (CBT), Acceptance and Commitment Therapy (ACT), Dialectical Behavior Therapy (DBT), and Prolonged Exposure (PE) for PTSD, Dr. Bolden is committed to evidence-based, effective treatment.

Beyond clinical work, she is deeply involved in community mental health, practitioner training, and research‚Äîwith a focus on ethnic disparities in mental health and culturally proficient care. As a co-founder of a multi-site private practice and mental health nonprofit, Dr. Bolden collaborates with agencies, universities, and professionals to enhance advocacy, treatment, and inclusion in the mental health field.
